"title": "7422: ritual",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7422",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The regulations governing Jewish religious life and worship, especially sacrifices, ritual cleanliness and food laws. By the sacrificial death of Jesus Christ these rituals have been fulfilled and play no part in the new covenant.</p>\n<h2>The purpose of ritual sacrifices</h2>\n<h3>To atone for sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:12-Lev5:13\">LEV 5:12–5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:38-Exod29:43\">EXO 29:38–29:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev1:3-Lev1:13\">LEV 1:3–1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:1-Lev4:3\">LEV 4:1–4:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:13-Lev4:14\">LEV 4:13–4:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:20-Lev4:23\">LEV 4:20–4:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:26-Lev4:28\">LEV 4:26–4:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev4:31-Lev4:35\">LEV 4:31–4:35</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev5:13\">LEV 5:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:1-Lev6:7\">LEV 6:1–6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:1-Lev7:7\">LEV 7:1–7:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:1-Lev16:34\">LEV 16:1–16:34</a></p>\n<h3>To maintain fellowship between God and his people</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev3:1-Lev3:5\">LEV 3:1–3:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:11-Lev7:15\">LEV 7:11–7:15</a> <em>The offering was part burnt and part eaten in a fellowship meal and expressed covenant relationship with God.</em></p>\n<h3>To express worship and gratitude to God</h3>\n<p>The grain offering was the only bloodless offering but it accompanied the other offerings and was burnt whole to express gratitude to God for the harvest and for particular blessings:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:1-Lev2:3\">LEV 2:1–2:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev2:8-Lev2:16\">LEV 2:8–2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev6:14-Lev6:23\">LEV 6:14–6:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev7:9-Lev7:10\">LEV 7:9–7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev9:4\">LEV 9:4</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num6:14-Num6:17\">NUM 6:14–6:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num28:3-Num28:13\">NUM 28:3–28:13</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals for purification from ritual uncleanness</h2>\n<h3>Childbirth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:22-Luke2:24\">LUK 2:22–2:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev12:1-Lev12:8\">LEV 12:1–12:8</a></p>\n<h3>Unclean diseases</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:40-Mark1:44\">MRK 1:40–1:44</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt8:2-Matt8:4\">MAT 8:2–8:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:12-Luke5:14\">LUK 5:12–5:14</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev14:2-Lev14:7\">LEV 14:2–14:7</a></p>\n<h3>Unclean discharges</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev15:32-Lev15:33\">LEV 15:32–15:33</a></p>\n<h3>Touching dead bodies</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num19:11-Num19:13\">NUM 19:11–19:13</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals relating to food</h2>\n<h3>Clean and unclean foods</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:1-Lev11:2\">LEV 11:1–11:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44-Lev11:47\">LEV 11:44–11:47</a></p>\n<h3>The eating of blood is forbidden</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen9:4-Gen9:5\">GEN 9:4–9:5</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev17:11-Lev17:12\">LEV 17:11–17:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts15:20\">ACT 15:20</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals relating to the priesthood</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev8:30\">LEV 8:30</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod29:1-Exod29:9\">EXO 29:1–29:9</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals relating to the place of worship</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr29:4-2Chr29:5\">2CH 29:4–29:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev16:15-Lev16:20\">LEV 16:15–16:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:62-1Kgs8:63\">1KI 8:62–8:63</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr7:4-2Chr7:5\">2CH 7:4–7:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra6:16-Ezra6:17\">EZR 6:16–6:17</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals relating to special days</h2>\n<h3>Festivals</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev23:37\">LEV 23:37</a></p>\n<h3>The Sabbath</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod31:12-Exod31:17\">EXO 31:12–31:17</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:2\">MAT 12:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:24\">MRK 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:2\">LUK 6:2</a></p>\n<h2>The initiation ritual of circumcision</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen17:10-Gen17:14\">GEN 17:10–17:14</a></p>\n<h2>Ritual only has meaning when accompanied by obedience</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:25\">ROM 2:25</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa1:11-Isa1:17\">ISA 1:11–1:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:16-Matt15:20\">MAT 15:16–15:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:18-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:18–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt23:25\">MAT 23:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:28-Rom2:29\">ROM 2:28–2:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:19\">1CO 7:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor8:8\">1CO 8:8</a></p>\n<h2>Rituals of the old covenant are fulfilled by Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:17\">COL 2:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:27-Mark2:28\">MRK 2:27–2:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:11\">COL 2:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:1-Heb10:3\">HEB 10:1–10:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb10:8-Heb10:10\">HEB 10:8–10:10</a></p>\n<h2>Old covenant rituals are abolished under the new covenant</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:10\">HEB 9:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:19\">MRK 7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts10:9-Acts10:15\">ACT 10:9–10:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom7:6\">ROM 7:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:14\">ROM 14:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom14:20\">ROM 14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:6\">GAL 5:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal6:15\">GAL 6:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:15\">EPH 2:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:13-Col2:16\">COL 2:13–2:16</a></p>",
